-- CORRECTED - Blast halts some production at Imperial Oil refinery
-- 
-- Thu Dec 14, 2006 9:28am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2006/12/14/refinery-explosion-unit-idUSTOR00142320061214

 

  (Corrects headline to make clear that only some of the
output at the refinery is affected) 

 TORONTO  Dec 14 (Reuters) - Imperial Oil Ltd. ( IMO.TO ) said
on Thursday an early morning explosion has halted production at
one of its hydrocracking units.  The unit, part of the oil company's massive refinery
complex in Sarnia, Ontario, upgrades about 18,000 barrels of
gasoil per day.


